Wash and dry all produce. Peel and halve @red onion{1}(halved). Mince enough so
that you have 1 TBSP minced onion. Slice remainder. Core, seed, and remove white
ribs from @red bell pepper{1}(cored and seeded), then thinly slice. Thinly slice
@radishes{3}(thinly sliced). Cut @lime{1}(cut in half) in half. Pick
@cilantro{1/4%oz}(leaves picked) leaves from stems. Finely chop half the leaves.

Drain @pineapple{4%oz}, then finely chop. In a #small bowl{}, stir together
pineapple, juice from one lime half, minced onion, and finely chopped cilantro.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Chop @chicken thighs{12%oz} into 1-inch pieces. In a #medium bowl{}, toss
chicken, @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, and salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{} in #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook,
tossing occasionally, until browned and no longer pink in center,
~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside in a #serving dish{} or #bowl{}.

Heat another drizzle of vegetable oil in same pan. Add pepper and sliced onion.
Cook, tossing occasionally, until softened and lightly browned,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{4} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave until warm and
soft, about ~{30%seconds}. Cut remaining lime half into 4 wedges.

Place chicken, pepper mixture, cilantro leaves, radishes, @sour cream{4%tbsp},
lime wedges, tortillas, and salsa in individual #serving plates{} or bowls and
invite everyone to assemble their own tacos.

> We encourage you to make a self-serve taco bar using this recipe's ingredients
> and let all of your hungry eaters fill their tortillas just the way they like.